<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-325] ACL section 23.1 in manual is outdated</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-325</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It appears that the Lustre manual content about ACLs is somewhat out of date.  The URL &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.suse.de/~agruen/acl/linux-acls/online/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://www.suse.de/~agruen/acl/linux-acls/online/&lt;/a&gt; no longer works (404 error) so a new source of Linux ACL documentation should be found, for example &lt;a href=&quot;https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-US/Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux/7/html/Storage_Administration_Guide/ch-acls.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-US/Red_Hat_Enterprise_Linux/7/html/Storage_Administration_Guide/ch-acls.html&lt;/a&gt; should be around for 10 years or so.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Secondly, the discussion of the client &lt;tt&gt;acl&lt;/tt&gt; option is outdated.  Since Lustre 2.7.0 the client &lt;tt&gt;acl&lt;/tt&gt; mount option is no longer available at all and will return an error instead of just printing a warning message that it is deprecated (since it has been deprecated since Lustre 1.8), so mention of mounting the client with &lt;tt&gt;noacl&lt;/tt&gt; should be removed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Instead, an example of mounting the MDS with &lt;tt&gt;noacl&lt;/tt&gt; should be added to allow disabling ACLs on a system-wide basis.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
